        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses the meaning of C. K. Sprengel’s term "dichogamy". Dichogamous plants are functionally monoecious; <hi rend="italic">Primula</hi> is functionally dioecious.</p>  
<p>Reports Hermann Crüger’s observations of <hi rend="italic">Cattleya</hi> and of bees pollinating <hi rend="italic">Catasetum</hi>. Crüger will observe Melastomataceae.</p> 
            <p>Has built a hothouse.</p> 
<p>Fears <hi rend="italic">Amsinckia</hi> cannot be dimorphic.</p>  
<p>Ill health slows his work on <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>.</p> 
        </abstract>
